Package: fluxcapacitoR
Type: Package
Title: Flux-Focused Age Modeling for Layered Sediments
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-06-12
Authors@R: c(
    person("Nicholas", "McKay" ,email = "nick@nau.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3598-5113")
    )
  )
Maintainer: Nick McKay <nick@nau.edu>
Description: An age modeling strategy focused on flux and accumulation
    rates in layered sediments. Builds varve-informed age-ensemble priors
    that combine low-frequency monotone spline fits to dated horizons
    with high-frequency simulated annual-layer (varve) variability,
    evaluates age ensembles against calibrated age distributions, and
    simulates synthetic varve thickness series with AR(1) or long-memory
    persistence. Part of the 'geoChronR' package family.
